<bioghist encodinganalog="545">
<p>Edward Dreier was a Grand Rapids, Michigan advertising photographer.</p>
</bioghist>



<scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
<p>The Dreier collection consists of photographs and negatives largely of Upper Peninsula views, primarily of the Pictured Rocks near Munising, of Grand Island, Marquette, Tahquamenon Falls, and the Keweenaw Peninsula. Included are photographs of car ferries and ferry docks at Mackinaw City and Saint Ignace.</p>
</scopecontent>

